    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Inomine sanctae et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/173">Otto</persName> dei gratia <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >rex</rs> Francorum et Langobardorum. Noverit igitur omnium fidelium
                        nostrorum industria, quia dilectus <rs key="#siblingOf">frater noster</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #siblingOf" ref="#people/175">Bruno</persName>
                        <rs key="#Intercessory">sugessit humiliter magestati</rs> nostrae pro quodam
                            <persName key="#Abbots"><name ref="Aupaldus">Aupaldo</name></persName>
                        venerabili <rs key="#Abbots">abbate</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/95"><rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                            confessoris Christi Ambrosii</orgName>, postulans ut eum pro nostre
                        merceedis incremento cum universis qui cum eo degunt famulis Christi
                        cunctaque venerandi cenobii substantia sub nostri <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">mundeburdi tuicionem</rs> susipere
                        dignaremur. Nos vero nostre mercedis amplificande gratia petitioni eius
                        asensum prebuimus rata et congrua suggerenti, suscipientes eum et omnes qui
                        ei commissi sunt servos dei cum universis ipsius sancti loci possessionibus
                        quantascumque deo auspice nunc habent aut in posterum habituri sunt, cum <rs
                            key="#Royal_slave">familiis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Personal_statuses">commendatitiis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Personal_statuses">cartulariis</rs> atque <rs key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldionibus utriusque sexus</rs>, eo tenore quo sub nostri regiminis
                        sint tutela nostreque providentie <rs key="#Immunity">inmunitate
                            perpetua</rs>. Confirmamus etiam <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/260">Lemuntam</geogName> predicto monasterio, sicuti dive
                        memorie <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/9">Lotharius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> per preceptum statuit suum, cum <rs
                            key="#Houses #Demesnes">casa indominicata</rs> et <rs key="#Churches"
                            >capellam</rs> ad se aspicientem in honore <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >sancti Genesii</orgName> dicatam nec non <rs key="#Oil">oliveta</rs>
                        vel <rs key="#Mansi">mansa sex</rs> in locis subnominatis:
                                <placeName><geogName key="#Mansi #Oil" ref="#estates/2375"
                                >Uilla</geogName></placeName>, <placeName><geogName
                                key="#Mansi #Oil" ref="#estates/2376"
                            >Sel[u]aniate</geogName></placeName>, <placeName><geogName
                                key="#Mansi #Oil" ref="#estates/2377"
                            >Madrunino</geogName></placeName>, <placeName><geogName
                                key="#Mansi #Oil" ref="#estates/2378"
                            >Cautunico</geogName></placeName>, <placeName><geogName
                                key="#Mansi #Oil" ref="#estates/2379">Ucto</geogName></placeName>,
                            <placeName ref="#places/574"><geogName key="#Mansi #Oil"
                                ref="#estates/2380">Ciuenna</geogName></placeName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs> et <rs key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldionibus et aldiabus</rs> ad eam curtem aspicientibus; confirmamus
                        insuper eidem monasterio sancti Ambrosii <rs key="#Mansi">mansa dua</rs>,
                        unum in <placeName><geogName
                                key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/2381">Melonico</geogName></placeName>, alium in <rs
                            key="#Villas">villa</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Mansi #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2382">Clepiate</geogName>, quod precessor noster <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/32">Karolus</persName> predicto loco
                        confirmavit; confirmamus etiam <rs key="#Curtes">curtes tres</rs>, unam que
                        dicitur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2373">Pasiliano</geogName> cum omnibus ad se pertinentibus
                        et curtem de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2372">Feliciano</geogName> cum omnibus ad se pertinentibus
                        et curtem de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/2374">Monte</geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Marquisâ€™/ducal/princely_diploma #Churches">capellis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Castle">castellis</rs> et omnibus ibidem aspicientibus, quos <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">reges</rs> clarissimi <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/79">Hugo</persName> et <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/72">Lotharius</persName> per sui precepti paginam eidem
                        loco pro remedio animarum illorum in proprium [tradi]derunt. Si quis autem
                        ex presulibus ducibus comitibus aut alicuius partis officialibus hanc
                        nostram regalis escellentie auctoritatem convictus fuerit violasse, <rs
                            key="#Penalty">duplam inmunitatis nostre penam, centum auri
                        pondera</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">predicto [loco]
                            componere compellatur</rs>. Et ut [ho]c regale preceptum pro futuris
                        tem[po]ribus atentius observetur, nostre manus inscriptione insignitam anulo
                        nostro iussimus adsignari. Signum domni Ottonis serenissimi regis (M.)
                            <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Bruno">Brun</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> advicem <persName
                            key="#Archchaplain"><name ref="Mannasei">Mannasei</name></persName>
                        <rs>archicappellani</rs> recognovi. (SI.Â 1.) (SR.) Data sexto idus octobris
                        anno incarnationis domini nostri Iesu Christi DCCCCLI, indictione X, anno
                        regni Ottonis regis in Francia XVI, in Italia I; actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/65">Papia</placeName>; in dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
